@*
    Site-wide "Ask" modal — opened by the header trigger ([data-ask-open]). Mirrors the command
    palette's overlay mechanics but is a separate surface (Q&A, not navigation). Ships hidden and
    is revealed by ask.js, so with JS disabled nothing shows (pure progressive enhancement — there
    is no server-rendered answer fallback). Conversation history is kept client-side and persists
    while the modal is open/closed within a page.
*@
<div class="ask-modal" data-ask hidden>
    <div class="ask-modal__backdrop" data-ask-close></div>
    <div class="ask-modal__dialog" role="dialog" aria-modal="true" aria-label="Ask about the site">
        <div class="ask-modal__head">
            <span class="ask-modal__title mono"><icon name="sparkle" size="18" /> Ask</span>
            <button type="button" class="ask-modal__close" data-ask-close aria-label="Close">
                <icon name="close" size="16" />
            </button>
        </div>

        <div class="ask-modal__thread" data-ask-thread aria-live="polite"></div>

        <div class="ask__bar">
            <span class="ask__prompt mono">&gt;</span>
            <input type="text"
                   class="ask__input mono"
                   data-ask-input
                   placeholder="Ask about Liam, his posts, or talks…"
                   autocomplete="off"
                   maxlength="500"
                   aria-label="Ask a question about the site" />
            <button type="button" class="ask__submit mono" data-ask-submit>Ask</button>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>
